plantuml_diagram:
@startuml
!define AWSPuml https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awslabs/aws-icons-for-plantuml/v20.0/dist
!include AWSPuml/AWSCommon.puml

title High-Level Deployment Architecture (FastAPI on AWS)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam wrapWidth 220
skinparam maxMessageSize 120

actor "Client" as client

node "AWS Cloud" as aws {
  node "VPC" as vpc {
    node "Public Subnet" as pub {
      node "Compute (Container Runtime)" as compute {
        artifact "FastAPI API Service\nPython + FastAPI/Starlette\nUvicorn\nPort: 8080" as api
      }
    }
  }

  database "(Optional) Managed Data Store\nNot detected in codebase" as db_opt
  storage "(Optional) Object Storage\nNot detected in codebase" as s3_opt
}

cloud "GitHub" as github {
  node "GitHub Actions CI/CD" as gha {
    artifact "Workflows\n- lint\n- build & push container\n- terraform deploy" as workflows
  }
}

client --> api : HTTPS (via load balancer / ingress)
workflows --> compute : Deploy container image\n(Terraform)
workflows --> aws : AWS API calls\n(assume role / access keys)

note right of api
Containerized web API.
Dockerfile runs Uvicorn and exposes 8080.
end note

note bottom of gha
CI/CD uses GitHub Actions to lint, build/push image,
and deploy infrastructure with Terraform.
end note

@enduml
